race.comment: Is today the day for ACT NATURAL (1), who has been placed in all eight of his starts? He's been close in stronger maidens than this and looks well placed. The only concern is the wide gate but he gets the services of Jacob Opperman, who can give him his chance. RATADASH (12) showed nice improvement between her first and second start and is open to even more improvement here. She's the map horse that can park just behind the speed and be strong late. She's a definite winning chance. ROYAL SCRIPTURE (6) bumped into some nice horses last campaign. He returns here off the back of a solid trial and can run well from a low draw. He's a must-include. STRONG MINDED (18) and BRIMARVI ROSEMARIE (9) have both shown glimpses of ability that will see them win a maiden soon. Both can be included in exotics and wider plays.
